00:14:31,890 --> 00:14:36,690
There must be a lot of people who remember last year's twin typhoon, Kaola.

178
00:14:36,690 --> 00:14:41,400
This typhoon is also small in scale, but a similar twin typhoon—

179
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:23,100
Wh-What's this?

180
00:15:23,100 --> 00:15:26,140
So there really was another Yoo Hyeon Jae!

181
00:15:26,140 --> 00:15:27,720
Whoa, Thumbs Up!

182
00:15:27,720 --> 00:15:30,910
What on earth? What are you?

183
00:15:30,910 --> 00:15:33,010
Don't be too shocked.

184
00:15:33,010 --> 00:15:37,500
Because I'm also you. That's not it, should I say that you are me?

185
00:15:37,500 --> 00:15:38,830
What?

186
00:15:38,830 --> 00:15:43,670
It must be difficult to believe, but I'm Yoo Hyeon Jae from 1993.

187
00:15:43,670 --> 00:15:45,950
1993?

188
00:15:45,950 --> 00:15:50,310
On that night in 1993 that you wanted so much to turn back,

189
00:15:50,310 --> 00:15:53,310
because of a strange typhoon, I went to the future for a bit and ended up coming back here.

190
00:15:53,310 --> 00:16:00,670
So that is, when you experience it yourself it's a really big deal. But now that I try to say it, it does sound quite strange, right?

191
00:16:00,670 --> 00:16:02,990
Well, so, uh.

192
00:16:07,060 --> 00:16:15,600
Anyway, in the end, you came here because of Mom and Dad's ashes?

193
00:16:15,600 --> 00:16:20,790
So this wasn't the worst-case scenario like I thought.

194
00:16:20,790 --> 00:16:22,170
What are you saying?

195
00:16:22,170 --> 00:16:25,250
You come out as having disappeared here, you see.

196
00:16:25,250 --> 00:16:29,560
So I was trying to stop you from coming here at any cost, but whoa!

197
00:16:29,560 --> 00:16:33,060
I didn't know I would end up meeting you here.

198
00:16:33,060 --> 00:16:37,020
Really, there must actually be a fate that is impossible to change.

199
00:16:49,370 --> 00:16:52,620
Then, you mean, you are me?

200
00:16:52,620 --> 00:16:55,740
That's what I'm saying. At first I was confused,

201
00:16:55,740 --> 00:16:58,820
but I figured it out when I saw the note you left at the bank.

202
00:16:58,820 --> 00:17:01,420
What note? What are you talking about?

203
00:17:01,420 --> 00:17:04,200
The money and the note you stored at the bank.

204
00:17:04,200 --> 00:17:07,290
You did that to give it to Gwang Jae, right?

205
00:17:07,290 --> 00:17:12,940
I did think about sending it to Gwang Jae. But how do you know this?

206
00:17:12,940 --> 00:17:15,320
I am you, for one,

207
00:17:15,320 --> 00:17:17,990
and I came from the future, I'm telling you. No.

208
00:17:17,990 --> 00:17:21,980
That's not it. That is, originally I came from the past.

209
00:17:21,980 --> 00:17:24,000
Anyway, that's how it is.

210
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:28,520
So that means you're me from 1993.

211
00:17:28,520 --> 00:17:32,100
On that night in 1993, we received the golden cup at the Gayo Top Ten.

212
00:17:32,100 --> 00:17:35,890
That evening you wanted so much to turn back.

213
00:17:36,900 --> 00:17:44,600
Right, on that night I ended up drifting away from all of them.

214
00:17:44,600 --> 00:17:50,600
I thought all of it was my money. But I guess it wasn't true.

215
00:17:53,520 --> 00:17:59,940
- So how are they living?
- What?

216
00:17:59,940 --> 00:18:03,580
You just said you saw the future?

217
00:18:03,580 --> 00:18:07,450
What about Bo Hee? Gwang Jae?

218
00:18:08,510 --> 00:18:13,570
Th-That is, umm. It's a bit of a long story.

219
00:18:13,570 --> 00:18:17,150
Well, I do tell stories excellently.

220
00:18:17,150 --> 00:18:20,020
Where should I start?

221
00:18:22,400 --> 00:18:26,300
Gwang Jae, Bo Hee and President Soon Tae, they were all living together.

222
00:18:26,300 --> 00:18:30,170
And Yeong Jae this guy, he was really successful.

223
00:18:34,830 --> 00:18:37,270
What's this? Who is it?

224
00:18:37,270 --> 00:18:40,170
He looks really similar to Hyeon Jae.

225
00:18:43,220 --> 00:18:48,600
Damn, this weather. At this rate, we might get struck by lightning.

226
00:18:48,600 --> 00:18:53,030
Our fans are still the same, even though twenty years have passed.

227
00:18:53,030 --> 00:18:56,840
They're as excellent as always, and amazing.

228
00:18:56,840 --> 00:19:03,120
They still remember you, and they still give love to our songs.

229
00:19:03,120 --> 00:19:04,950
Is that so?

230
00:19:11,920 --> 00:19:14,820
Roar! ... Moo...

231
00:19:14,820 --> 00:19:17,180
It looks like I don't have much time left.

232
00:19:17,180 --> 00:19:18,930
What?

233
00:19:18,930 --> 00:19:20,380
It's nothing.

234
00:19:20,380 --> 00:19:25,390
About Ji Hoon. Can you tell me more?

235
00:19:25,390 --> 00:19:29,040
What? I told you!

236
00:19:29,040 --> 00:19:31,990
He's quite an okay guy.

237
00:19:31,990 --> 00:19:37,420
Of course, he must be excellent since he's my son.

238
00:19:37,420 --> 00:19:41,930
Right. He was really excellent.

239
00:19:41,930 --> 00:19:47,900
Righteous to the point it's frustrating. Clever to the point of causing jealousy.

240
00:19:47,900 --> 00:19:53,400
He also sings and dances fairly well. More than well enough to stand on stage.

241
00:19:53,400 --> 00:19:57,480
With that, he could be full of himself, but he isn't at all, this kid.

242
00:19:57,480 --> 00:20:00,990
And studying? Is he good at studying?

243
00:20:00,990 --> 00:20:05,090
He went to the best university in the country.

244
00:20:05,090 --> 00:20:09,090
He takes after me so he got smart brains.

